Dear Mathew,=0D=0A=0D=0AA live pig is placed on a surgical table at the Med=
ical College of Wisconsin=E2=80=A6we=E2=80=99ll call him Henry.=0D=0A=0D=0A=
Surgeons-in-training cut into Henry=E2=80=99s chest. They insert tubes. The=
y remove organs. They keep him alive until the end of the training course=
=E2=80=94that=E2=80=99s if Henry survives the invasive procedures.=0D=0A=0D=
=0AThis is happening right now=E2=80=94in the name of medicine.=0D=0A=0D=0A=
Almost no other medical centers in the U.S. and Canada use this cruel and e=
ducationally inferior practice.=0D=0A=0D=0ABefore the next training session=
 begins=E2=80=94and more animals die=E2=80=94please raise your voice with t=
he Physicians Committee. Urge MCW to stop killing animals to train surgeons=
=2E=0D=0A=0D=0AIt=E2=80=99s time they join the 238 other general surgery pr=
ograms in the U.S. and Canada that use only human-based methods!=0D=0A=0D=
=0ATAKE ACTION=0D=0A=0D=0AYou can help stop this cruelty. We=E2=80=99ve suc=
ceeded before, and right now, we have momentum on our side:=0D=0A=0D=0AEarl=
ier this month, you helped us stop Brown University from killing animals to=
 train emergency medicine doctors!=0D=0ALast year, you helped end the use o=
f animals to train surgeons at St. Elizabeth Youngstown Hospital AND the Un=
iversity of Arizona!=0D=0AJust recently, we advanced initiatives in the Wis=
consin legislature that would prohibit the use of animals for medical train=
ing if non-animal methods are available OR an equivalent program in the sta=
te teaches without animals. Both apply in the case of MCW.=0D=0APlease send=
 a message right away, Mathew. Help end this cruelty and advance ethical an=
d effective medicine.=0D=0A=0D=0AAnimal lives are at risk. Thank you for ta=
king action today.=0D=0A=0D=0ASincerely,=0D=0A=0D=0A=09=0D=0ANeal Barnard, =
MD=0D=0APresident, PCRM=0D=0A=0D=0AP.S. Yale, Stanford, and the Mayo Clinic=
 all use only human-based practices. Across the U.S. and Canada, 78% of sur=
veyed general surgery programs use non-animal methods. Tell the Medical Col=
lege of Wisconsin that cutting up live animals for medical training is both=
 cruel and unnecessary. Take action today, before the next training session=
 begins.=0D=0A=0D=0APhysicians Committee for Responsible Medicine=0D=0A5100=
 Wisconsin Ave NW=0D=0AWashington, DC 20016=0D=0AUnited States=0D=0AUnsubsc=
